  "body": "# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nValidator will monitor the network at least 1 epoch before starting attestation, just to make sure there is no duplicate validator running somewhere\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\nadd a safety start switch:\r\n` --delay-attestation=x `\r\nwhere x is the number of epochs that the validator will monitor the network for its duplication attestation before starting to attest\r\n\r\n### Reason\r\nI'm afraid that I accidentally start my validator when it's actually already running on the same machine or somewhere else.\r\nFor example: I migrate my server to another one and forget to stop the validator (or it's set to start automatically on reboot)\r\n",
